<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="41" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,373,919]" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis box="[197,369,413,438]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">Male genitalia</emphasis>
: Subgenital plates rather rounded laterally and caudally. Style with slightly curved slender apophysis with hair-like setae basally and stout setae apically, preapical lobe poorly developed. Aedeagus similar to previous species, but apex of shaft, with dorsal acute hook-like projection, in lateral view.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,373,919]" box="[197,1163,533,559]" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis box="[197,397,533,558]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">Female genitalia</emphasis>
: Median lobe of seventh sternite with a strong median concavity.
</paragraph>
